<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
<head>

</head>

<body>
	
 <ul>
	<li>
		<h3>Creating/Updating themes</h3>
		<p>Visit http://2134125.appspot.com/update_theme?label=<b><i>YOURLABEL</b></i>&width=<b><i>XXX</b></i>&height=<b><i>YYY</b></i></p>
		<p>replace YOURLABEL with the name of your theme, and the height and width you want associated with it</p>
		<p>On submitting the request you should see: <b><i>saved theme YOURLABEL ( XXX, YYY ) </b></i></p>
		<p>Updating a theme will reset any old values with the new height and width</p>
		<p>Try it here;</p>
		<p>
			<a href='http://2134125.appspot.com/update_theme?label=NEWLABEL&width=400&height=200'>
				http://2134125.appspot.com/update_theme?label=NEWLABEL&width=400&height=200
			</a>
		</p>
		<p>
			<a href='http://2134125.appspot.com/themes'>
				<h3>Existing Themes</h3>
			</a>
		</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h3>Getting themed images</h3>
		<p>As src value to img tags, just use 
			http://2134125.appspot.com/serve_themed?theme=<b></>YOURLABEL</b></i>&image_id=<b><i>YOUR_ID</b></i> 
		</p>
		<p>
			if no label is passed, the default theme is <b><i>'default'</b></i>
		</p>
		<p>E.G.</p>
		<p>Default<br/>
			http://2134125.appspot.com/serve_themed?image_id=1<br/>
			<img src='http://2134125.appspot.com/serve_themed?image_id=1' alt='demo image' />
		</p>
		<p>With New Label<br/>
			http://2134125.appspot.com/serve_themed?theme=NEWLABEL&image_id=1<br/>
			<img src='http://2134125.appspot.com/serve_themed?theme=NEWLABEL&image_id=1' alt='demo image' />
		</p>			
	</li>
	<li>
		<h3><a href='http://2134125.appspot.com/test'>view unit tests</a></h3>
	</li>	
</body>
</html>
